<Author>ticex
<Content>A class above other Mercure Hotels - Great Value, Loved it! I've stayed at the Mercure Berlin Tempelhof Airport several times over the past years with the latest visit being for the bargain price of only 鈧?5! At this kind of price it has to be one of the best value hotels I've ever stayed in. The rooms are exceptionally clean and in superb condition (mine even had a kitchenette!), the beds are large and very comfortable and the bathroom is spotlessly clean and of a good size.Worth noting if you're arriving with a car is it's free to park on the street 2 minutes walk away but failing that the hotel offers an underground garage for about 鈧?0 per night.You know what to expect when staying at a Mercure in Germany but this one is a cut above the others I've stayed at and will always be my first choice when staying in Berlin. 
