<Author>daSVGrouch
<Content>Where is my room? I booked several days in advance, prepaying the room on AmEx Axiom. When I arrived, I completed the registration, and then was advised that they acknowledged the reservation, but had no rooms. The desk clerk summoned the manager. The manager found another room at the Accor Suite Hotel, and explained that not only was it 8 euros cheaper, it was also closer to the ITB conference. I replied that I was not attending ITB, and my client was just south of Tempelhof (THF). She arranged a taxi, and claimed she provided a voucher to the alternate hotel, and a second voucher from the alternate hotel to my appointment. However, the next day I learned that the second voucher was actually only a part of the first, and paid the fare myself. 
