<Author>Cauchemar
<Content>An Enjoyable Stay This hotel made a perfect base for our long weekend in Berlin. Having landed at Tegel airport a bus and a couple of underground trains got us to a few hundred meters from the hotel. The staff were very friendly and helpful when asked for advise. The rooms were very clean and well finished. Noise was not an issue at all with no sound traveling from adjacent rooms or from outside.The breakfasts were first class with a wide selection of dishes to choose from and was open until 11:00. The gym is fairly small but has modem equipment and two separate showers. The sauna gave us a nice relaxing end to the day and was free. 
